    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Quercus lyrata, native to lowland wetlands in the southeastern United States, from Delaware and southern Illinois south to northern Florida and southeast Texas. It is used for flooring, furniture, and heavy construction.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
